 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search MRM Senior Vice President of Artificial Intelligence Non-Model Review and Challenge Citi 18,274 reviews Queens, NY Citi 18,274 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. MRM Senior Vice President of Artificial Intelligence Non-Model Review and Challenge 
This position is part of the Artificial Intelligence (AI) Review and Challenge Group within Citi’s Model Risk Management organization. This position will report to the MRM Director of Artificial Intelligence (AI) Review and Challenge and will manage a group of reviewers to perform independent review and effective challenge across the lifecycle of Artificial Intelligence (AI) / Machine Learning (ML) non-model objects 
Responsibilities: 
Manage a group of reviewers to perform independent review and effective challenge across the lifecycle of Artificial Intelligence (AI) / Machine Learning (ML) non-model objects 
Oversee the group’s work to ensure adherence to applicable policies, procedure, templates, and testing guidance to manage the risk of all aspects of the AI/ML non-model objects 
Interact with key stakeholders such as AI/ML owners / developers, Citi AI/ML Center of Excellence, internal management of businesses and functions, internal audit, and regulators regarding AI/ML related matters 
May participate in capacity planning, team building (hiring, training, coaching, and management). 
Contribute to strategic, cross-functional initiatives within the model risk management organization 
Qualifications: 
Advanced degree (Master’s and above) is required in the fields of mathematics, statistics, computer science, engineering, data science, AI/ML, etc. 
7+ years experience in financial services or related industries 
Analytical expertise with AI / ML applications in banking or related industries 
Experience / familiarity with AI / ML applications in areas such as cybersecurity, chatbot, natural language processing, image / voice recognition, robotic process automation 
In-depth technical knowledge of common AI/ML techniques and strong understanding of risks associated with AI/ML and corresponding mitigants 
Ability to develop and manage a team 
Ability to manage relationships with internal businesses and functions, control groups and external regulators 
Ability to deliver compelling presentations and influence executive audiences. Excellent communications skills with ability to engage and inspire team forward
 Ability to drive innovation via thought leadership while maintaining end-to-end view 
